{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Review the performance and correctness of the changes in iteration 26 of the title-extractor.\n\n## Context\n- This code runs on a mobile device (React Native / Expo) — total title extraction must complete under 10 seconds\n- The improvement plan is at tools/title-loop/docs/26-e8ee23c/improvement-plan.md\n- Focus on lib/text-classifier/title-extractor.ts and lib/text-classifier/food-dictionary.ts\n\n## Key changes to review (from git diff HEAD~1):\n\n### 1. food-dictionary.ts: Added ~30 common title words (prepositions, adjectives, short food terms, Polish words)\n\n### 2. title-extractor.ts changes:\n- `startsWithNumber`: Added Unicode fraction characters (½⅓⅔¼¾ etc.)\n- New `CATEGORY_SECTION_LABELS` set + `isCategorySectionLabel()` function — food-group labels that may appear as last word of compound title\n- New `extractContentWords()` + `passesCorroboration()` — checks if candidate's vocabulary appears elsewhere in document\n- New `isBodyProse()` — detects lowercase prose lines (4+ words)\n- `isTitleAbsentPage`: Now also checks for body prose\n- `findBurstEnd`: Improved spillover handling — tracks consecutive blanks, stops at ALL_CAPS lines\n- Caps-coalescing merge: Relaxed section-label block when next line is a single-word category label completing a short (2-4 word) fragment\n- First-after-preamble bonus: Now checks `isSectionLabel` in preceding filter, uses 0.12 bonus for structural preambles (vs 0.08), caps combined positional boost at 0.15\n- Pre-threshold artifact filtering: Removes ALL_CAPS candidates that fail corroboration before computing threshold\n- Multi-title assembly: Added corroboration filtering for ALL_CAPS candidates, uses `startsWithNumber` instead of `/^\\s*\\d/`\n\n## Performance focus areas:\n1. `passesCorroboration` does O(words × lines) string matching — is this acceptable for mobile?\n2. `extractContentWords` is called potentially multiple times — any redundancy?\n3. The corroboration filtering runs twice (pre-threshold AND multi-title assembly) — is this intentional/needed?\n4. `findBurstEnd` changes — any risk of infinite loops or excessive scanning?\n5. Overall: do these changes add meaningful latency to the 10-second budget?\n\n## Correctness focus areas:\n1. The caps-coalescing relaxation: operator precedence in the condition — is the `||` / `&&` grouping correct?\n2. `passesCorroboration` threshold logic: 100% for ≤3 words, 67% for longer — does this match the improvement plan?\n3. The positional boost cap at 0.15 — is `baseScoreBeforePositionalBonuses` captured at the right point?\n4. `isBodyProse` regex — does `[a-ząćęłńóśźż]` correctly match Polish lowercase letters?\n5. Pre-threshold corroboration: the safety check `remainingCaps.length >= 2` — could this leave artifacts when there are exactly 2 ALL_CAPS candidates?\n\nPlease read the actual source files to verify your analysis. Return specific findings with file:line references."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_014ZeYx2KMUHyi6o55JfXJ1N","session_id":"80bb29ff-3467-4b06-a8e7-a7aec63d83fa","uuid":"e72e7540-cc2f-4fde-896e-905ea87b156b"}
