{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_0133P19M1rSeTMKMTSjeZaR3","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I now have a thorough picture of the implementation and the test file. Let me compile the complete analysis.\n\n---\n\n# Code Review: Test Coverage for Iteration 26 Changes\n\n## Review Metrics\n- **Files Reviewed**: 3 (test file, source file, improvement plan)\n- **Tested features (with dedicated coverage)**: 2 of 8\n- **Missing test coverage**: 6 of 8 new features\n- **Plan-specified test cases added**: 0 of 5\n- **Plan-specified edge cases added**: 0 of 4\n\n## Executive Summary\n\nNone of the 5 unit test cases and none of the 4 edge cases listed in the improvement plan's \"Testing Strategy\" section were added to the test file. Six of the eight newly implemented features have zero dedicated test coverage. The two existing corroboration tests (lines 380–469) cover multi-title post-selection corroboration but do not reach the new pre-threshold artifact filtering path, which has a distinct triggering condition.\n\n---\n\n## Coverage Findings by Feature\n\n### 1. `startsWithNumber` — Unicode fraction support\n\n**Status: NOT TESTED**\n\nThe test at line 85 (`\"skips lines starting with numbers\"`) uses `\"12\\nApple Pie\"` — a plain ASCII digit. The new regex extension covers `½⅓⅔¼¾⅕⅖⅗⅘⅙⅚⅛⅜⅝⅞`. No test exercises any of these characters.\n\nPlan test case 3 (`\"½ red onion, thinly sliced\"` → `startsWithNumber` returns true) was not added. The function is not exported so it can only be tested end-to-end, but even the integration path is untested: there is no test case where a line beginning with a Unicode fraction is the first line and a title appears after it.\n\nThe `extractTitle` (heuristic) suite at line 60 would be the natural home for this, since it tests `startsWithNumber` behavior directly via `\"skips lines starting with numbers\"`.\n\n### 2. `CATEGORY_SECTION_LABELS` and caps-coalescing merge relaxation\n\n**Status: NOT TESTED**\n\nThe existing test at line 322 (`\"short-caps merge breaks at a section label\"`) verifies the opposite: that `INGREDIENTS` blocks a merge. No test covers the new relaxation for single-word category labels (e.g. `VEGETABLES`) when preceded by a short 2–4 word ALL_CAPS fragment.\n\nPlan test case 2 (`LEMON HERB ROASTED` + `VEGETABLES` → merged as `LEMON HERB ROASTED VEGETABLES`) was not added.\n\nThe safety condition — that a 5+ word preceding fragment should NOT merge — is also untested (improvement plan edge case 1: `\"Vegetable Soup\"` followed by standalone `VEGETABLES`).\n\nPlan edge case 3 (`SKŁADNIKI` at line 2 following a complete title → should NOT merge) is also untested.\n\n### 3. `passesCorroboration` — pre-threshold artifact filtering\n\n**Status: PARTIALLY COVERED, NEW PATH UNTESTED**\n\nThe existing corroboration block (lines 380–469) tests post-selection multi-title corroboration (the path at source line ~1395–1400). The new iteration 26 change adds a **second, earlier call** to `passesCorroboration` at source line 1210, inside the pre-threshold scoring block. This path fires only when `allCapsInScored.length >= 2` and removes artifacts before the threshold is computed.\n\nThe two existing tests use inputs where both titles genuinely pass corroboration, so they exercise the happy path but not the pre-threshold removal logic. The key scenario to test — an artifact title whose early-position bonus inflates the threshold and causes a legitimate title later in the document to fall below it — has no test case. This is the exact failure mode that motivated the change (plan section \"Fix 3 / Pre-threshold artifact filtering\").\n\nThe third corroboration test (`\"does not apply corroboration to single-title pages\"`, line 450) correctly verifies that single-title pages are unaffected, and that boundary still holds. But there is no test for the intermediate case: an artifact is removed pre-threshold, leaving exactly 2 remaining ALL_CAPS candidates that then proceed normally.\n\n### 4. `isBodyProse`\n\n**Status: NOT TESTED**\n\nThe function is not exported and has no test that exercises it. Plan test case 4 (`\"Reduce heat and stir...\"` followed by more body text → `isTitleAbsentPage` returns true) was not added.\n\n### 5. `isTitleAbsentPage` — body prose detection added\n\n**Status: NOT TESTED**\n\nThere are no tests for `isTitleAbsentPage` at all in the file — neither before nor after iteration 26. The function gates behavior in `extractTitleWithEmbeddings` (line 895) but no test exercises a mid-recipe page scenario.\n\nPlan test case 4 (prose-start page) is missing. Plan edge case 2 (`½ cup` as first ingredient but with a title on line 0 → `isTitleAbsentPage` must NOT fire) is missing. Plan edge case 4 (body prose on lines 0–2 but valid title at position 0 that passes hard filters → iteration 23 fallback must still fire) is missing.\n\n### 6. `findBurstEnd` — consecutive-blank and ALL_CAPS heading termination\n\n**Status: NOT TESTED (new behavior)**\n\nThe existing test at line 169 (`\"skips burst of short lines at start\"`) exercises the short-garbled-line skip path. It does not exercise the new overflow-marker branch with the consecutive-blank (`consecutiveBlanks >= 2`) or ALL_CAPS-heading (`isAllCaps(lineText) && wordCount(lineText) >= 2`) termination conditions.\n\nPlan test case 5 (input with `[CORRUPTED SPILLOVER...]` followed by body text then a title at line 10 → title correctly extracted) was not added. The `SPILLOVER` keyword in `OVERFLOW_MARKERS` has no test at all.\n\n### 7. First-after-preamble bonus strengthening and cap\n\n**Status: NOT TESTED**\n\nThe bonus was changed from a flat +0.08 to a conditional +0.08/+0.12 split (plain empty preamble vs. structural preamble containing section labels or metadata). The +0.15 combined cap was also added. No test verifies:\n- That a structural preamble (section label before the title) produces +0.12\n- That a plain empty preamble produces +0.08\n- That when the candidate-relative position bonus also fires, the combined boost is capped at +0.15\n\n### 8. Food dictionary expansion (`COMMON_TITLE_WORDS` merged into `FOOD_DICTIONARY`)\n\n**Status: NOT TESTED**\n\nPlan test case 1 (`\"Bra1sed Cod w1th Wh1te W1ne\"` → repaired to `\"Braised Cod with White Wine\"`) was not added. The `repairOcrText` / `repairOcrWord` function is not exported, and there is no integration-level test where the repair of a common preposition like `with` determines the winning candidate.\n\n---\n\n## Specific Gaps to Fill\n\nListed in priority order by failure-mode coverage value:\n\n**Gap 1 — `startsWithNumber` with Unicode fractions (integration)**\nAdd to the heuristic `extractTitle` suite:\n```typescript\nit(\"skips lines starting with Unicode fractions\", () => {\n  expect(extractTitle(\"½ red onion, thinly sliced\\nApple Pie\")).toBe(\"Apple Pie\");\n  expect(extractTitle(\"¼ cup flour\\nChocolate Cake\")).toBe(\"Chocolate Cake\");\n});\n```\nAnd a corresponding `extractTitleWithEmbeddings` case where the fraction line would otherwise be position 0.\n\n**Gap 2 — `isTitleAbsentPage` mid-recipe detection**\nThis function is called in `extractTitleWithEmbeddings` but has no test. Two cases are needed:\n\n- Prose start: three lowercase body-prose lines → extractor returns `undefined`\n- Guard: body prose on lines 0–2 but a valid title at position 0 that passes hard filters → extractor still returns the title (iteration 23 fallback must not be suppressed)\n\n```typescript\nit(\"returns undefined for mid-recipe page starting with body prose\", async () => {\n  const embed = createMockEmbed([], []);\n  const text = [\n    \"reduce heat and stir the mixture slowly\",\n    \"add more stock if the risotto looks dry\",\n    \"season with salt and pepper to taste\",\n    \"CARPACCIO DI PESCE SPADA\",\n  ].join(\"\\n\");\n  expect(await extractTitleWithEmbeddings(text, embed)).toBeUndefined();\n});\n```\n\n**Gap 3 — caps-coalescing merge relaxation for category section labels**\nTwo new cases needed in the existing short-caps-merge suite:\n- `LEMON HERB ROASTED` + `VEGETABLES` → `LEMON HERB ROASTED VEGETABLES`\n- `CHICKEN NOODLE SOUP INGREDIENTS` (5-word preceding fragment + `VEGETABLES`) → no merge\n\n**Gap 4 — pre-threshold artifact filtering**\nThe distinction from the post-selection corroboration path is subtle but important. Add a case where the artifact's bonus would have inflated the threshold without pre-filtering:\n```typescript\nit(\"pre-threshold artifact removal prevents threshold inflation\", async () => {\n  // \"XYZ ARTIFACT\" has no vocabulary support; without pre-removal its early\n  // position bonus pushes the threshold above \"REAL RECIPE TITLE\"'s score.\n  const embed = createMockEmbed([\"real recipe title\"], []);\n  const input = [\n    \"XYZ ARTIFACT\",\n    // ... body text with no xyz/artifact words ...\n    \"REAL RECIPE TITLE\",\n    // ... body text corroborating real recipe title ...\n  ].join(\"\\n\");\n  expect(await extractTitleWithEmbeddings(input, embed)).toBe(\"REAL RECIPE TITLE\");\n});\n```\n\n**Gap 5 — `findBurstEnd` spillover handling**\nAdd a test where `SPILLOVER` in the first line causes the extractor to skip several body-text lines and pick up the title after a double blank or ALL_CAPS heading:\n```typescript\nit(\"skips corrupted spillover preamble and finds title after blank cluster\", async () => {\n  const embed = createMockEmbed([\"beef stew\"], []);\n  const text = [\n    \"[CORRUPTED SPILLOVER from page 14]\",\n    \"place in a large pot and cover with water\",\n    \"bring to a boil then reduce heat\",\n    \"\",\n    \"\",\n    \"Beef Stew\",\n    \"Ingredients\",\n    \"500g beef\",\n  ].join(\"\\n\");\n  expect(await extractTitleWithEmbeddings(text, embed)).toBe(\"Beef Stew\");\n});\n```\n\n**Gap 6 — first-after-preamble bonus differentiation**\nAt minimum, add a test confirming the structural preamble case (section label before the first candidate) results in the title winning:\n```typescript\nit(\"strengthens bonus when preamble contains section label (Pattern D type)\", async () => {\n  const embed = createMockEmbed([\"halibut with saffron cream sauce\"], []);\n  const text = \"FISH & SEAFOOD\\nHalibut with Saffron Cream Sauce\\nIngredients\\n2 fillets\";\n  expect(await extractTitleWithEmbeddings(text, embed)).toBe(\"Halibut with Saffron Cream Sauce\");\n});\n```\n\n---\n\n## Strengths\n\n- The three existing corroboration tests (lines 380–469) are well-structured and cover the happy path, the artifact-rejection path, and the single-title boundary correctly.\n- The mock embed design (title words, header words, neutral vector) is expressive enough to test all the new features above without changes to the mock itself.\n- The `_resetEmbeddingCacheForTests()` call in `beforeEach` is consistently applied and prevents inter-test contamination.\n\n## Systemic Pattern\n\nEvery iteration adds new heuristic functions but the test file has not grown to match. The improvement plan's \"Testing Strategy\" section explicitly lists specific test cases to add, but in iteration 26 none were added. This is a recurring pattern: iteration 25 also added `passesCorroboration` and the corroboration tests were added, but the pre-threshold reuse of the same function in iteration 26 went untested. Consider making it a definition-of-done requirement that plan-listed test cases are committed in the same iteration as the implementation."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a678c63137f965e11 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 47321\ntool_uses: 12\nduration_ms: 104507</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"80bb29ff-3467-4b06-a8e7-a7aec63d83fa","uuid":"4ab6b7d5-adb2-488d-b9b4-aa743d407641","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Review the test coverage for the iteration 26 changes in the title-extractor.\n\n## Context\n- Test file: lib/text-classifier/__tests__/title-extractor.test.ts\n- Source: lib/text-classifier/title-extractor.ts\n- Improvement plan: tools/title-loop/docs/26-e8ee23c/improvement-plan.md\n\n## New functionality added in iteration 26:\n1. `startsWithNumber` now handles Unicode fractions (½⅓⅔¼¾ etc.)\n2. `CATEGORY_SECTION_LABELS` — food-group labels allowed in compound titles\n3. `passesCorroboration` — vocabulary corroboration for multi-title filtering\n4. `isBodyProse` — lowercase prose line detection\n5. `isTitleAbsentPage` — now includes body prose detection\n6. `findBurstEnd` — improved spillover handling with consecutive blank tracking\n7. Caps-coalescing merge relaxation for category section labels\n8. First-after-preamble bonus strengthening + cap\n9. Pre-threshold artifact filtering\n\n## Testing focus:\n1. Which of these new features have dedicated test coverage?\n2. Which are MISSING test coverage?\n3. The improvement plan's \"Testing Strategy\" section lists specific test cases to add — were they added?\n4. Are the existing corroboration tests (lines 380-469) sufficient for the new pre-threshold corroboration?\n5. Edge cases from the improvement plan's \"Edge cases to verify\" section — are they tested?\n\nRead both the test file and improvement plan to verify. List specific gaps.","agentId":"a678c63137f965e11","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I now have a thorough picture of the implementation and the test file. Let me compile the complete analysis.\n\n---\n\n# Code Review: Test Coverage for Iteration 26 Changes\n\n## Review Metrics\n- **Files Reviewed**: 3 (test file, source file, improvement plan)\n- **Tested features (with dedicated coverage)**: 2 of 8\n- **Missing test coverage**: 6 of 8 new features\n- **Plan-specified test cases added**: 0 of 5\n- **Plan-specified edge cases added**: 0 of 4\n\n## Executive Summary\n\nNone of the 5 unit test cases and none of the 4 edge cases listed in the improvement plan's \"Testing Strategy\" section were added to the test file. Six of the eight newly implemented features have zero dedicated test coverage. The two existing corroboration tests (lines 380–469) cover multi-title post-selection corroboration but do not reach the new pre-threshold artifact filtering path, which has a distinct triggering condition.\n\n---\n\n## Coverage Findings by Feature\n\n### 1. `startsWithNumber` — Unicode fraction support\n\n**Status: NOT TESTED**\n\nThe test at line 85 (`\"skips lines starting with numbers\"`) uses `\"12\\nApple Pie\"` — a plain ASCII digit. The new regex extension covers `½⅓⅔¼¾⅕⅖⅗⅘⅙⅚⅛⅜⅝⅞`. No test exercises any of these characters.\n\nPlan test case 3 (`\"½ red onion, thinly sliced\"` → `startsWithNumber` returns true) was not added. The function is not exported so it can only be tested end-to-end, but even the integration path is untested: there is no test case where a line beginning with a Unicode fraction is the first line and a title appears after it.\n\nThe `extractTitle` (heuristic) suite at line 60 would be the natural home for this, since it tests `startsWithNumber` behavior directly via `\"skips lines starting with numbers\"`.\n\n### 2. `CATEGORY_SECTION_LABELS` and caps-coalescing merge relaxation\n\n**Status: NOT TESTED**\n\nThe existing test at line 322 (`\"short-caps merge breaks at a section label\"`) verifies the opposite: that `INGREDIENTS` blocks a merge. No test covers the new relaxation for single-word category labels (e.g. `VEGETABLES`) when preceded by a short 2–4 word ALL_CAPS fragment.\n\nPlan test case 2 (`LEMON HERB ROASTED` + `VEGETABLES` → merged as `LEMON HERB ROASTED VEGETABLES`) was not added.\n\nThe safety condition — that a 5+ word preceding fragment should NOT merge — is also untested (improvement plan edge case 1: `\"Vegetable Soup\"` followed by standalone `VEGETABLES`).\n\nPlan edge case 3 (`SKŁADNIKI` at line 2 following a complete title → should NOT merge) is also untested.\n\n### 3. `passesCorroboration` — pre-threshold artifact filtering\n\n**Status: PARTIALLY COVERED, NEW PATH UNTESTED**\n\nThe existing corroboration block (lines 380–469) tests post-selection multi-title corroboration (the path at source line ~1395–1400). The new iteration 26 change adds a **second, earlier call** to `passesCorroboration` at source line 1210, inside the pre-threshold scoring block. This path fires only when `allCapsInScored.length >= 2` and removes artifacts before the threshold is computed.\n\nThe two existing tests use inputs where both titles genuinely pass corroboration, so they exercise the happy path but not the pre-threshold removal logic. The key scenario to test — an artifact title whose early-position bonus inflates the threshold and causes a legitimate title later in the document to fall below it — has no test case. This is the exact failure mode that motivated the change (plan section \"Fix 3 / Pre-threshold artifact filtering\").\n\nThe third corroboration test (`\"does not apply corroboration to single-title pages\"`, line 450) correctly verifies that single-title pages are unaffected, and that boundary still holds. But there is no test for the intermediate case: an artifact is removed pre-threshold, leaving exactly 2 remaining ALL_CAPS candidates that then proceed normally.\n\n### 4. `isBodyProse`\n\n**Status: NOT TESTED**\n\nThe function is not exported and has no test that exercises it. Plan test case 4 (`\"Reduce heat and stir...\"` followed by more body text → `isTitleAbsentPage` returns true) was not added.\n\n### 5. `isTitleAbsentPage` — body prose detection added\n\n**Status: NOT TESTED**\n\nThere are no tests for `isTitleAbsentPage` at all in the file — neither before nor after iteration 26. The function gates behavior in `extractTitleWithEmbeddings` (line 895) but no test exercises a mid-recipe page scenario.\n\nPlan test case 4 (prose-start page) is missing. Plan edge case 2 (`½ cup` as first ingredient but with a title on line 0 → `isTitleAbsentPage` must NOT fire) is missing. Plan edge case 4 (body prose on lines 0–2 but valid title at position 0 that passes hard filters → iteration 23 fallback must still fire) is missing.\n\n### 6. `findBurstEnd` — consecutive-blank and ALL_CAPS heading termination\n\n**Status: NOT TESTED (new behavior)**\n\nThe existing test at line 169 (`\"skips burst of short lines at start\"`) exercises the short-garbled-line skip path. It does not exercise the new overflow-marker branch with the consecutive-blank (`consecutiveBlanks >= 2`) or ALL_CAPS-heading (`isAllCaps(lineText) && wordCount(lineText) >= 2`) termination conditions.\n\nPlan test case 5 (input with `[CORRUPTED SPILLOVER...]` followed by body text then a title at line 10 → title correctly extracted) was not added. The `SPILLOVER` keyword in `OVERFLOW_MARKERS` has no test at all.\n\n### 7. First-after-preamble bonus strengthening and cap\n\n**Status: NOT TESTED**\n\nThe bonus was changed from a flat +0.08 to a conditional +0.08/+0.12 split (plain empty preamble vs. structural preamble containing section labels or metadata). The +0.15 combined cap was also added. No test verifies:\n- That a structural preamble (section label before the title) produces +0.12\n- That a plain empty preamble produces +0.08\n- That when the candidate-relative position bonus also fires, the combined boost is capped at +0.15\n\n### 8. Food dictionary expansion (`COMMON_TITLE_WORDS` merged into `FOOD_DICTIONARY`)\n\n**Status: NOT TESTED**\n\nPlan test case 1 (`\"Bra1sed Cod w1th Wh1te W1ne\"` → repaired to `\"Braised Cod with White Wine\"`) was not added. The `repairOcrText` / `repairOcrWord` function is not exported, and there is no integration-level test where the repair of a common preposition like `with` determines the winning candidate.\n\n---\n\n## Specific Gaps to Fill\n\nListed in priority order by failure-mode coverage value:\n\n**Gap 1 — `startsWithNumber` with Unicode fractions (integration)**\nAdd to the heuristic `extractTitle` suite:\n```typescript\nit(\"skips lines starting with Unicode fractions\", () => {\n  expect(extractTitle(\"½ red onion, thinly sliced\\nApple Pie\")).toBe(\"Apple Pie\");\n  expect(extractTitle(\"¼ cup flour\\nChocolate Cake\")).toBe(\"Chocolate Cake\");\n});\n```\nAnd a corresponding `extractTitleWithEmbeddings` case where the fraction line would otherwise be position 0.\n\n**Gap 2 — `isTitleAbsentPage` mid-recipe detection**\nThis function is called in `extractTitleWithEmbeddings` but has no test. Two cases are needed:\n\n- Prose start: three lowercase body-prose lines → extractor returns `undefined`\n- Guard: body prose on lines 0–2 but a valid title at position 0 that passes hard filters → extractor still returns the title (iteration 23 fallback must not be suppressed)\n\n```typescript\nit(\"returns undefined for mid-recipe page starting with body prose\", async () => {\n  const embed = createMockEmbed([], []);\n  const text = [\n    \"reduce heat and stir the mixture slowly\",\n    \"add more stock if the risotto looks dry\",\n    \"season with salt and pepper to taste\",\n    \"CARPACCIO DI PESCE SPADA\",\n  ].join(\"\\n\");\n  expect(await extractTitleWithEmbeddings(text, embed)).toBeUndefined();\n});\n```\n\n**Gap 3 — caps-coalescing merge relaxation for category section labels**\nTwo new cases needed in the existing short-caps-merge suite:\n- `LEMON HERB ROASTED` + `VEGETABLES` → `LEMON HERB ROASTED VEGETABLES`\n- `CHICKEN NOODLE SOUP INGREDIENTS` (5-word preceding fragment + `VEGETABLES`) → no merge\n\n**Gap 4 — pre-threshold artifact filtering**\nThe distinction from the post-selection corroboration path is subtle but important. Add a case where the artifact's bonus would have inflated the threshold without pre-filtering:\n```typescript\nit(\"pre-threshold artifact removal prevents threshold inflation\", async () => {\n  // \"XYZ ARTIFACT\" has no vocabulary support; without pre-removal its early\n  // position bonus pushes the threshold above \"REAL RECIPE TITLE\"'s score.\n  const embed = createMockEmbed([\"real recipe title\"], []);\n  const input = [\n    \"XYZ ARTIFACT\",\n    // ... body text with no xyz/artifact words ...\n    \"REAL RECIPE TITLE\",\n    // ... body text corroborating real recipe title ...\n  ].join(\"\\n\");\n  expect(await extractTitleWithEmbeddings(input, embed)).toBe(\"REAL RECIPE TITLE\");\n});\n```\n\n**Gap 5 — `findBurstEnd` spillover handling**\nAdd a test where `SPILLOVER` in the first line causes the extractor to skip several body-text lines and pick up the title after a double blank or ALL_CAPS heading:\n```typescript\nit(\"skips corrupted spillover preamble and finds title after blank cluster\", async () => {\n  const embed = createMockEmbed([\"beef stew\"], []);\n  const text = [\n    \"[CORRUPTED SPILLOVER from page 14]\",\n    \"place in a large pot and cover with water\",\n    \"bring to a boil then reduce heat\",\n    \"\",\n    \"\",\n    \"Beef Stew\",\n    \"Ingredients\",\n    \"500g beef\",\n  ].join(\"\\n\");\n  expect(await extractTitleWithEmbeddings(text, embed)).toBe(\"Beef Stew\");\n});\n```\n\n**Gap 6 — first-after-preamble bonus differentiation**\nAt minimum, add a test confirming the structural preamble case (section label before the first candidate) results in the title winning:\n```typescript\nit(\"strengthens bonus when preamble contains section label (Pattern D type)\", async () => {\n  const embed = createMockEmbed([\"halibut with saffron cream sauce\"], []);\n  const text = \"FISH & SEAFOOD\\nHalibut with Saffron Cream Sauce\\nIngredients\\n2 fillets\";\n  expect(await extractTitleWithEmbeddings(text, embed)).toBe(\"Halibut with Saffron Cream Sauce\");\n});\n```\n\n---\n\n## Strengths\n\n- The three existing corroboration tests (lines 380–469) are well-structured and cover the happy path, the artifact-rejection path, and the single-title boundary correctly.\n- The mock embed design (title words, header words, neutral vector) is expressive enough to test all the new features above without changes to the mock itself.\n- The `_resetEmbeddingCacheForTests()` call in `beforeEach` is consistently applied and prevents inter-test contamination.\n\n## Systemic Pattern\n\nEvery iteration adds new heuristic functions but the test file has not grown to match. The improvement plan's \"Testing Strategy\" section explicitly lists specific test cases to add, but in iteration 26 none were added. This is a recurring pattern: iteration 25 also added `passesCorroboration` and the corroboration tests were added, but the pre-threshold reuse of the same function in iteration 26 went untested. Consider making it a definition-of-done requirement that plan-listed test cases are committed in the same iteration as the implementation."}],"totalDurationMs":104507,"totalTokens":47321,"totalToolUseCount":12,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1019,"cache_read_input_tokens":43219,"output_tokens":3082,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1019},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
